labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the extent, intensity, timing and method of reproduction in fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes) including fecundity, reproductive rates, spawning, and nursery grounds.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the vertical distance (height or elevation) of river or lake water from a specified point of reference to the water's surface. Rivers are defined as being upstream from the tidal limit.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Physical, chemical or optical properties of individual solid particles.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Raw direct output parameters from microstructure sensors, probes or profilers that are used to determine the distribution of water body properties on a millimetric scale.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters associated with seafloor landforms and features such as bedforms, seamounts and ridges, including morphology, evolution and associated transport phenomena.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for trace metalloid elements and inorganic selenium species in water occupying the space between sediment grains. Trace metalloids are considered as B, Ge, As, Sb, Te, and Po (but not Si which is classed separately because of its major role in environmental chemistry).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for trace metalloid elements and inorganic selenium species in either whole organisms or their constituent parts. Trace metalloids are considered as B, Ge, As, Sb, Te, and Po (but not Si which is classed separately because of its major role in environmental chemistry).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of total, organic and inorganic phosphorus per unit weight of sediment.  Sediment is understood to be the solid phase of the bed, including the recently settled material sometimes known as fluff collected from the bed surface.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the quantification of fluxes of any gaseous species from water column to atmosphere including parameters characterising closely related processes such as bubble formation in the surface layer.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the distribution of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae)at a particular time and location, including presence/absence indicators.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All organometallic and orgamometalloid compound concentration parameters (including saturations for gaseous species) in all phases of sediments (including pore waters)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all variants of chlorophyll expressed in terms of per unit volume, per unit area of any body of fresh or salt water, or as a relative colour index (e.g. PCI). Does not include data expressed per unit mass of SPM.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Ammonium and ammonia concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All organosulphur and organoselenium compound concentration parameters (including saturations for gaseous species) in all phases of any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All organometallic and organometalloid compound concentration parameters (including saturations for gaseous species) in all phases of any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing aspects of a geologic unit that are the result of bulk chemical, mineralogical or physical changes related to change in the physical or chemical environment.  Includes weathering, supergene alteration, hydrothermal alteration and metasomatic effects not considered metamorphic.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying rates associated with nitrification (oxidation of reduced nitrogen such as ammonium) and denitrification (conversion of nitrate into gaseous compounds such as nitric oxide, nitrous oxide and molecular nitrogen) processes in the water column of any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to kill other life forms in suspended particulate material (SPM) collected by water column filtration, centrifugation or sediment trapping. Only includes parameters expressed per unit mass of SPM and not per unit volume of the water column.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of metal elements per unit weight of sediment.  Sediment is understood to be the solid phase of the bed, including the recently settled material sometimes known as fluff collected from the bed surface.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the health and conservation status of coral species and coralligenous habitats.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing usage of Fish Aggregating Devices (FAD) in fisheries (particularly purse seine tuna fisheries).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of adenylates (ADP, ATP etc) in all phases of the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the reproduction of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the actions or reactions, usually in response to the environment, of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the size, shape or physiological activity including disease and parasite infection status of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the causes and rate of mortality of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Qualitative and quantitative parameters related to the sampling activity; includes terms related to sampling effort, sampling gears, sample processing.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the abundance and nature of material classed as refuse introduced to the environment by activities of man that are not covered by the more specific P02 terms for micro-litter (UMLS and UMLW), beach litter (BLIT) or seafloor litter (SLIT).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the abundance and nature of litter data collected on the seabed.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the abundance and nature of debris released on coastlines.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any quantification of the mass (e.g. carbon, nitrogen, weight) of microalgae present on hard substrate or soft sediment at the bottom of any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that quantify the size, shape, age and life processes (including mortality) of fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that quantify the numbers of fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes) at a given location in any body of salt or fresh water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that quantify the numbers or amount of living material of shellfish (molluscs - including cephalopods - and crustaceans of interest to fisheries research and commercial fisheries) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that quantify the size, shape, age and life processes (including mortality) of shellfish (molluscs - including cephalopods - and crustaceans of interest to fisheries research and commercial fisheries).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that quantify the fecundity, reproductive rates or nature of reproduction in shellfish (molluscs - including cephalopods - and crustaceans of interest to fisheries research and commercial fisheries).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters derived from flow cytometry data analysis of water samples using in situ or bench-top flow cytometers.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the abundance and nature of microscopic particles of man-made materials and in particular microplastics present in the sediment.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the abundance and nature of microscopic particles of man-made materials and in particular microplastics present in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any quantification of the number (e.g. count, abundance) of microalgae present on hard substrate or soft sediment at the bottom of any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration (not 380nm light absorption) parameters for dissolved or total organic matter (includes humics, yellow matter, Gelbstoff) in any body of salt or fresh water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that quantify any attribute of a biological entity specified elsewhere in the data model and therefore do not map to the existing biologically classified P02 categories. This concept is used as a temporary grouping of parameter codes created for the SeaDataNet biological standard format.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Stable isotope parameters (concentrations, ratios and enrichments) in sediment, including biota-associated parameters such as isotope enrichment in foraminifera tests.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Stable isotope parameters (concentrations, ratios and enrichments) in both the dissolved and particulate phases of any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Stable isotope parameters (concentrations, ratios and enrichments) in secondary mineral deposits in caves. This includes stalactites, stalagmites, flowstone, and crystal growths.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Stable isotope parameters (concentrations, ratios and enrichments) in either the solute or solvent phase of sediment pore waters.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Stable isotope parameters (concentrations, ratios and enrichments) from measurements on living (at the time of sampling) organisms or parts thereof.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Stable isotope parameters (concentrations, ratios and enrichments) in both the gaseous and aerosol phases of the atmosphere.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Stable isotope parameters (concentrations, ratios and enrichments) in frozen precipitation (snow, hail, ice and slush), its accumulations (e.g. glaciers), sea ice and frozen fresh water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All parameters associated with radioactivity in any body of fresh or salt water, including radiation counts, isotope activities and activity ratios. Activities per unit mass of SPM are included.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All parameters associated with radioactivity in the atmosphere, including radiation counts, isotope activities and activity ratios.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Bird (Class Aves) abundance per unit area (of land or sea) presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chondrichthyes) ash-free dry weight biomass per unit area of bed (sea, river, lake etc.) parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  Includes animals normally considered as planktonic if they have been returned from sediment samples.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chondrichthyes) abundance per unit area of bed (sea, river, lake etc.) parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  Includes animals normally considered as planktonic if they have been returned from sediment samples.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes) count parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards. Count includes presence/absence indicators.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Insect (Class Insecta) and earthworm (Subclass Oligochaeta) abundance per unit area of bed (sea, river, lake etc.) parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  Includes animals normally considered as planktonic if they have been returned from sediment samples. This parameter group has been implemented to separate predominantly freshwater taxa from predominantly marine taxa.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Insect (Class Insecta) and earthworm (Subclass Oligochaeta) ash-free dry weight biomass per unit area of bed (sea, river, lake etc.) parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  Includes animals normally considered as planktonic if they have been returned from sediment samples. This parameter group has been implemented to separate predominantly freshwater taxa from predominantly marine taxa.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Insecta abundance parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Insecta carbon biomass parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Microzooplankton carbon biomass parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards., but exclude morphological classifications such as 'heterotrophic flagellate'.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Bacteria ash-free dry weight biomass in sediment parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  The taxa may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.  Bacteria are defined as all taxa that fall into Kingdom Monera in the ITIS taxonomy, which includes cyanobacteria.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Basically any bacteria carbon biomass parameters that aren't included in parameter group BATC because they cannot be mapped to specific taxa in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  Bacteria are defined as Kingdom Monera, which includes cyanobacteria.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Bacteria carbon biomass parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.  Bacteria are defined as all taxa that fall into Kingdom Monera in the ITIS taxonomy, which includes cyanobacteria.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Microzooplankton biovolume parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS. These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Microzooplankton surface area per unit volume of the water column parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) carbon biomass parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) nitrogen biomass parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) abundance parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zoobenthos wet weight biomass per unit area parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  Includes animals considered as planktonic if they have been returned from sediment samples.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zoobenthos count parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.  These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards. Count includes presence/absence indicators.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All parameters (including concentration, saturation, turnover and fluxes) for dissolved oxygen in sediment and sediment pore waters.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for trace metalloid elements and inorganic selenium species in the particulate phase of any body of fresh or salt water collected by fitration, centrifugation or sediment trapping. Trace metalloids are considered as B, Ge, As, Sb, Te and Po (but not Si which is classed separately because of its major role in environmental chemistry).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for trace metalloid elements and non-organic selenium species in the dissolved phase of any body of fresh or salt water. This may include a contribution from the particulate phase if this has not been totally removed by filtration and the metalloid in question is reactive (ie detected as if it were dissolved) to the analytical technique used. Trace metalloids are considered as B, Ge, As, Sb, Te, and Po (but not Si which is classed separately because of its major role in environmental chemistry).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Metal concentrations in either whole organisms or their constituent parts.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Carbonate system parameters (DIC/TCO2, pH, alkalinity, pCO2) in sediment pore waters

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters used to characterize and monitor biological invasion by non-native organisms.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters identifying or quantifying zooplankton gut pigments

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that characterize or quantify the contents of the stomach and gut of an animal or group of animals.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Raw pH parameter output from any type of pH sensor.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Insect (Class Insecta) and earthworm (Subclass Oligochaeta) ash-free dry weight biomass per unit area of the littoral zone (between spring tide high and low water) parameters.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Insect (Class Insecta) and earthworm (Subclass Oligochaeta) abundance per unit area of the littoral zone (between spring tide high and low water) parameters.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any zoobenthos ash-free dry weight biomass per unit area of the littoral zone (between spring tide high and low water) parameters that are not fish or terrestrial animals (insecta/oligochaeta)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any zoobenthos abundance per unit area of the littoral zone (between spring tide high and low water) parameters that are not fish or terrestrial animals (insecta/oligochaeta)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters associated with the quantification of primary production by plants living on (e.g. corals, seaweed and seagrass) or in (e.g. benthic diatoms) the seabed.  Primary production is defined as the fixation of carbon dioxide into either organic or inorganic carbon by living entities and so includes photosynthesis and calcification.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measurements made at a given time of any state variable in a sample that is the subject of an experiment that will change the composition over time, such as the water sample in an incubation experiment.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters indicating the health of zooplankton and zoobenthos taxa, such as fecundity, egg condition, presence of parasites/diseases etc.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the extent or direction of atmospheric movement. Obvious examples are wind velocity, windspeed and wind direction, but can also include derived parameters such as force, energy, power and power density.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that quantify or classify the physical or financial resources used in fishing activities

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the number of birds (Class Aves) in a survey but not expressed per unit area. Includes presence/absence indicators.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of naturally-produced organic (molecules containing carbon) compounds that are built from multiple instances of structural units (monomers) that are covalently-bonded to produce larger structures in any sediment (material collected by a corer including fluff). Includes polynucleotides (RNA and DNA), polypeptides and polysaccharides (e.g. cellulose).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of naturally-produced organic (molecules containing carbon) compounds that are built from multiple instances of structural units (monomers) that are covalently-bonded to produce larger structures in any body of salt or fresh water. Includes polynucleotides (RNA and DNA), polypeptides and polysaccharides (e.g. cellulose).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Raw parameters (voltages and counts) from in-situ suspended particulate material sensors including transmissometers, nephelometers,in-situ particle sizers and ABS (including ADCP echo intensity).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measurements of the displacement of the water column surface from a fixed, stable reference expressed as either total pressure or sea pressure

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any quantification of the dry mass of zoobenthos (animals living on, in or near the bed of any water body). Includes animals normally considered planktonic if collected in sediment and data expressed ash-free and in terms of carbon, nitrogen etc..

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters (including geometries, labels and categorizations) relating to areas where authorities have and-or excercise specific rights or obligations.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of alkenones (unsaturated aliphatic ketones) and alkenoates (carboxylic acid esters) in any unconsolidated sediment including fluff.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Aliphatic hydrocarbon (alkane, alkene, alkyne, polycyclic aliphatics like hopane, terpenes etc.)  concentrations in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff'

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of carbohydrates, phenols, alkanols (alcohols), aldehydes and simple (non-alkenone) ketones in all phases of any body of fresh or salt water

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of carbohydrates, phenols, alkanols (alcohols), ethers,aldehydes and simple (non-alkenone) ketones in unlithified sediment (material collected by a corer including fluff).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the rate of alkenones (unsaturated aliphatic ketones) and alkenoates (carboxylic acid esters) sinking as particles through any body of water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of alkenones (unsaturated aliphatic ketones) and alkenoates (carboxylic acid esters) in all phases of the water column.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Lipids are defined as small water-insoluble biomolecules including fats, fatty acids, esters, sterols, isoprenoid compounds, etc..  Biota includes any type of sample originating from a living organism.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Lipids are defined as small water-insoluble biomolecules including fats, fatty acids, esters, sterols, isoprenoid compounds, etc..  Sediment is defined as material collected by a corer (including fluff).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Lipids are defined as small water-insoluble biomolecules including fats, fatty acids, esters, sterols, isoprenoid compounds, etc..  Water body includes any body of fresh or salt water. As lipids are insoluble in water the concencentrations are associated with the particulate phase.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: A measure of the tendency of any body of fresh or salt water to either gain or lose electrons when it is subject to change by introduction of a new species.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the extent and nature of recreational activities in coastal waters, estuaries and their margins such as beaches.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of compounds that lower the surface tension of a liquid, the interfacial tension between two liquids, or that between a liquid and a solid in any body of salt or fresh water. The term surfactants includes detergents, wetting agents, emulsifiers, foaming agents and dispersants.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying metal and metalloid fluxes as element concentration or isotope activities per unit area per unit time

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the electrical properties of geological units in the field. Includes parameters used to determine resistivity structure for shallow sediment properties, porosities and presence of hydrocarbon (CSEM), deeper crust and mantle studies (Magnetotellurics) and ore body location (polarisation).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of organic compounds containing both a carboxyl group and an amino group (including compounds such as salts and esters) sinking vertically as particles through a unit area of a water body in units time.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to compounds containing two oxygen atoms joined by a single bond but no carbon atoms in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the variety of entity types encountered in a population of living organisms

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the study of human interaction with the sea through the investigation of associated physical remains, be they vessels, shore side facilities, port-related structures, cargoes, human remains or submerged landscapes

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration of alkanols, phenols and ethers per unit mass or unit volume of sediment (material collected by a corer including fluff)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for organic sulphur species in ice

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Nitrate concentration parameters in ice. Includes nitrate+nitrite, which is often loosely referred to as nitrate.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for inorganic sulphur species in ice

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of halogens as elements or their inorganic compounds in ice

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to physical properties (e.g. colour, density, in-situ temperature) or characteristics (e.g. sea ice type) of any kind of water sample that was in its solid state at the time of sampling or measurement

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the chemical composition of any kind of water sample that was frozen solid at the time of sampling or measurement

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measurements of quantity (mass), thickness and spatial extent of snow and ice

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any parameters quantifying the magnetic (e.g. magnetic susceptibility), electrical (e.g. resistivity) or acoustic (e.g. P-wave propogation speed) of sediment or rock cores and samples

labels.name: definition
labels.original: 'Other' (not alkanes, alkenes, alkynes or PAHs) hydrocarbon concentration parameters (including saturation of gaseous species) in all phases of the atmosphere.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the rates of creation and consumption of volatile halocarbons (compounds comprising carbon atoms covalently bonded to fluorine, chlorine, bromine or iodine atoms) other than tracers (i.e. freons/chlorofluorocarbons) and contaminants in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of volatile halocarbons (compounds comprising carbon atoms covalently bonded to fluorine, chlorine, bromine or iodine atoms) other than tracers (i.e. freons/chlorofluorocarbons) and contaminants in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fluxes of species other than metals and nutrients between the bed (ie the sediment) and the water column sometimes termed benthic fluxes or sediment demand

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All concentration parameters for inorganic dissolved gases other than oxygen and the noble gases in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Uptake of nutrients other than nitrogen species (ie phosphate and silicate) by the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Statistical parameters derived from wave data expressing wave properties other than height, period and direction

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All concentration parameters for inorganic dissolved gases other than oxygen and the noble gases in sediment pore water samples

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Bucket group for parameters that cannot be classified elsewhere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: 'Other' (not alkanes, alkenes, alkynes or PAHs) hydrocarbon concentration parameters (including saturation of gaseous species) in all phases of the water column.  Does not include parameters expressed per unit weight of SPM.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the volume of water passing through a point in a river system per unit time, including the rates of freshwater, dissolved material and particulate load discharge from a river into the sea.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that describe the distribution of the degree of hotness within geologic units of lithified sedimentary, igneous of metamorphic rock.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of the elements classically regarded as major (>1% by weight as oxide: namely: Si, Ti, Al, Fe3+, Fe2+, Mg, Mn, Ca, Na, and K) plus affiliated parameters such as H2O- (adsorbed water) and H2O+ (or loss on ignition) in rocks or sediments.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for silicon species (including opal) in sediment (anything collected by a corer including fluff)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for metalloid elements in sediment.  Sediment is understood to be the solid phase of the bed, including the recently settled material sometimes known as fluff collected from the bed surface. Metalloids are considered as B, Ge, As, Sb, Te and Po (but not Si which is classed separately because of its major role in environmental chemistry)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of halogens as elements or simple inorganic compounds (eg iodate) in sediments (anything collected by a corer including fluff

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters specifying the proportions of inorganic components (major/minor/trace elements, trace metals etc.) in sediment or rock samples.  Major elements includes the H2O+ and H2O- parameters reported by convention in oxide weight per cent geochemical major element analyses.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that describe the the mass per unit volume of any samples of rock or unlithified sediment.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that describe the distribution of the degree of hotness within a body of rock or unlithified sediment.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameterisations of the intensity and inclination of Earth's magnetic field

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the  flux of thermal energy within the solid Earth or between the solid Earth and water bodies or atmosphere.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the level of radioactive emissions from in-situ geologic units

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any parameters quantifying ionising radiation emitted by cores or samples comprising rock, sediment (including surface sediment such as fluff)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per square metre) of viruses in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per square metre) of animals living on or near the seabed designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration of bacteria (Kingdom Monera so includes cyanobacteria) designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total) in any soil or sediment.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration of bacteria (Kingdom Monera so includes cyanobacteria) designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration of bacteria (Kingdom Monera so includes cyanobacteria) designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus, family) in any soil or sediment.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration of bacteria (Kingdom Monera so includes cyanobacteria) designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus, family) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per litre) of macroalgae (seaweeds) designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total) in any fresh or salt water body.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per litre) of microzooplankton (free swimming heterotrophic organisms smaller than 200um) designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total) in any fresh or salt water body.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per litre) of microzooplankton (free swimming heterotrophic organisms smaller than 200um) designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus or family) in any fresh or salt water body.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration (e.g. count, abundance) of free-floating autotrophic biological entities designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. microphytoplankton, ciliate, flagellate) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration (e.g. count, abundance) of free-floating autotrophic biological entities designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus, family) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per square metre) of animals living on or near the seabed designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any parameterisation of cell volume of free-floating autotrophic biological entities designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus, family) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any parameterisation of cell surface area of free-floating autotrophic biological entities designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus, family) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any parameterisation of biomass (e.g. wet weight, dry weight, carbon, nitrogen etc.) of free-floating autotrophic biological entities designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. microphytoplankton, ciliate, flagellate) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any parameterisation of biomass (e.g. wet weight, dry weight, carbon, nitrogen etc.) of free-floating autotrophic biological entities identified by their taxonomic names (e.g. family, genus, species) in any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the amount in a sample of a tracer (rhodamine, SF6, 3He, etc.) that has been purposely released into  a water body to track water mass movements or quantify exchanges with the atmosphere.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters characterising the environment in which sediments were deposited either by observation or interpretation of sedimentary rocks and unlithified sediments.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters characterising structure in sedimentary rocks and unlithified sediment such as bedding, lamination and bioturbation.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing or quantifying the mineralogical composition of rocks and unlithified sediments.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying and describing biota take by fishing activities

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) nitrogen biomass per unit volume parameters not included in group ZCTC.  Usually used for generic names such as 'mesozooplankton'.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the properties of rocks and sediments that are relevance to engineering such as physical strength and load-bearing capacity.  Includes the disciplines of rock mechanics and soil mechanics.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of halogens as elements or their inorganic compounds in all phases of any body of fresh or salt water

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of halogens as elements or their inorganic compounds in all phases of the atmosphere.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of halogens as elements or their inorganic compounds in all phases of sediment pore water

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that specify the number of specified members of Order Cetacea present at a particular time and location, including presence/absence indicators.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All measurements of the quantity or mass of any organometallic compound in any living organisms or their component parts

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the mass of fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes)in total or by species per unit area or per unit volume in any body of fresh or salt water expressed in any form (e.g. wet weight, dry weight, carbon, nitrogen, etc.).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters specifying the physical dimensions of the particles comprising lithified sedimentary rocks (including expressions of shape such as aspect ratio) and statistics derived from their variation in a sample (e.g. mean, mode, sorting, skewness).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that describe the degree to which sedimentary, igneous or metamorphic rocks are able to conduct heat

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that describe the degree to which unlithified sediment is able to conduct heat

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parmeters describing the space for fluids or gases within a geologic unit comprising lithified sediments, igneous rock or metamorphic rock.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to structure beneath sea-bed determined by the reflection of seismic energy along multiple parallel tracks.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to structure beneath sea-bed determined by the reflection of seismic energy along a single track.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the magnitude of naturally occurring low frequency earth movements such as used for earthquake seismology and natural noise studies.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the magnitude of earth movements resulting from artificial sources (such as explosions) far away from the measurement site.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measured or stratigraphically estimated ages of lithified sediments, igneous rock or metamorphic rock.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters specifying the physical dimensions of the particles comprising unlithified sediment (including expressions of shape such as aspect ratio) and statistics derived from their variation in a sample (e.g. mean, mode, sorting, skewness).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for metal elements in the combined dissolved and particulate phases of any body of fresh or salt water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to kill other life forms in either whole organisms or their constituent parts.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to kill other life forms in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff'.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to kill other life forms in either solution or suspension (i.e.includes measurements in both the dissolved and particulate phases) in any body of salt or fresh water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to modify bodily function or diagnose, cure, mitigate, treat, or prevent disease in either whole organisms or their constituent parts.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to modify bodily function or diagnose, cure, mitigate, treat, or prevent disease in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff'.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to modify bodily function or diagnose, cure, mitigate, treat, or prevent disease in either solution or suspension (i.e.includes measurements in both the dissolved and particulate phases) in any body of salt or fresh water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for carbon compounds regarded as environmentally harmful in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff' that are not included in other specific categories

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for carbon compounds regarded as environmentally harmful in solution or suspension (i.e.includes measurements in both the dissolved and particulate phases) in any body of salt or fresh water that are not included in other specific categories

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for carbon compounds regarded as environmentally harmful in either whole organisms or their constituent parts that are not included in other categories

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the uptake rate of nitrogen from excretion products (ammonium and urea) by flora and fauna living in any body of salt or fresh water

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the uptake rate of nitrate or gaseous nitrogen by flora and fauna living in any body of salt or fresh water

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that classify cloud cover into types such as cumulus and cirrus.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of chlorofluorocarbons (also known as freons or CFCs) in sny body of water

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Development stage parameters (such as proportion but excluding abundance or biomass) of zooplankton and zoobenthos. Benthic and planktonic animals have not been seggregated because there is a degree of overlap (eg shrimps).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of groundwater in a given system such as aquifer water level and rate of flow of water through rock formations.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the chemistry of terrestrial groundwater bodies such as aquifers and waters percolating through rock formations.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all parameters covering the strength of emitted microwave radiation return, including absolute measurements of returning signal strength as well as parameters expressed as backscatter (the proportion of transmitted signal returned)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Digital images of the water column obtained using either still or video cameras

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Digital images of the seabed obtained using either still or video cameras

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the location, nature and extent of objects that pose a threat to travel on the water column such as wrecks and obstructions

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying fauna and flora that indicate physical or chemical conditions in the water column such as colonisation depths and abundance of indicator species.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of organic compounds containing both a carboxyl group and an amino group dissolved in a body of water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters used to encode information specifying access rights to data, usually in terms of authorised roles

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the upward and downward motion of objects mounting sensors or collecting samples.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of organic compounds containing both a carboxyl group and an amino group in unlithified seabed material.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of organic compounds containing both a carboxyl group and an amino group in solids suspended in a body of water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: The identity of the parameter is not declared.  Covers cases such as internal working parameters and dummy channels.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration of any chemical species in water collected from the atmosphere.  Includes rain, snow, hail and fog but excludes cloud samples or snow accumulations on the ground.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to diseases and parasites of macroalgae (Rhodophycota, Chromphycota, Chlorophycota)  and seagrass (Charophyta, Anthophyta) and damage to seagrass beds

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the concentration of acids containing a carboxyl (-C(=O)OH) group, their anions or their salts in any phase of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying and describing the release of substances into the atmosphere as a result of human activity

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying concentrations of organic contaminants (substances regarded as harmful) other than PCBs and PAHs in all phases of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon (PAH) concentrations in all phases of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying polychlorobiphenyl (PCB) concentrations in all phases of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the effects of substances on living organisms.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the actions or reactions of birds (Class Aves), usually in response to the environment. Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the reproduction of birds (Class Aves)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the capture of non-target species during commercial and non-commercial fishing trips

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the reproduction of cetaceans (Order Cetacea)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quanitifying the transfer of substances considered harmful from land to sea, including river discharge rates of contaminant species (but not freshwater discharge rates).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the actions or reactions of fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chondrichthyes), usually in response to the environment. Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the infection of Fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes) by parasites and disease. Includes visual assesements and analytical data.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the extent, intensity, timing and method of fisheries

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that quantify the level of industrial activity or industrial output

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that quantify and specify material output into the environment as a result of industrial activity

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the accidental spillage of liquid or dry pollutants from vessels or marine industries. Parameters may include quantities of pollutant, areas affected and event duration.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the abundance of reptiles (Class Reptilia)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to diseases and parasites of reptiles (Class Reptilia)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the reproduction of reptiles (Class Reptilia)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the level of activity moving people or cargo from one place to another.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton and larger, exclusing fish, mammals, reptiles and insects) biomass determined by weighing unprocessed catch samples.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: PAH concentrations in suspended particulate material, regarded as anything sampled by a water bottle, SAP, sediment trap etc.  This group is for SPM composition measurements (concentration per unit weight) and NOT concentrations per unit volume of the water column in the particulate phase.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: PCB concentrations in suspended particulate material, regarded as anything sampled by a water bottle, SAP, sediment trap etc.  This group is for SPM composition measurements (concentration per unit weight) and NOT concentrations per unit volume of the water column in the particulate phase.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: PAH concentrations in all phases of the water column. This group includes concentrations per unit volume of the water column in the particulate phase, but not concentrations per unit wieght of SPM.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: PCB concentrations in all phases of the water column. This group excludes SPM composition measurements (concentration per unit weight).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fluxes of particulate total, organic and inorganic carbon (including as CaCO3) and nitrogen (often measured as 'total' but assumed to be 'organic'). Organic matter is defined as matter lost on ignition.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes) abundance per unit volume parameters not included under FATX.  Most commonly used for the generic term 'fish' that maps to multiple taxa.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes) size and shape parameters not included under FATM.  Most commonly used for the generic term 'fish' that maps to multiple taxa.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Deprecated term from a misguided attempt to distinguish between NO3 and NO3+NO2 for discovery. Use parameter group NTRA instead

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the volume, mass or thickness of particulate material that gathers on the seabed per unit time.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the irradiance of the sun impinging on the Earth's surface in the visible and infra-red waveband, generally accepted as wavelengths between 300 and 3000 nm

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the degree of hotness of the atmosphere.  Specifically excludes indirect measurements of other parameters such as wet bulb temperatures.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all parameters covering the strength of electromagnetic radiation signal return, including absolute measurements of returning signal strength as well as parameters expressed as backscatter (the proportion of transmitted signal returned)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of metal elements in suspended particulate material collected by water column filtration, centrifugation or sediment trapping. Deprecated as semantic overlap with MTWP.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for metallic elements in the particulate phase of the water column collected by fitration, centrifugation or sediment trapping

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for metallic elements in ice and snow

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration of metal elements in any phase of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the hydrogen ion concentration in water bodies

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the amount of liquids (e.g. ship's ballast) or solids (e.g. dredge spoil) deposited into the water column as a result of man's activities

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameterisations that describe climatic conditions in the past.  Includes climate indices, climate indicators and indirect measurements of climate-related phenomena such as sea level and water table depth.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the proportion of organic material in a soil or sediment sample

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying uncategorised organic substance concentrations in atmospheric, generally aerosol, samples such as organic matter and DOC.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters specifying the physical or chemical environment of a place where an organism is found.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters specifying the vertical and horizontal spatial extent of the ecological character of a place where an organism is found

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the causes and rate of mortality in cetaceans (Order Cetacea). Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the abundance and nature of bacteria (Kingdom Monera) infecting other biota.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the actions or reactions of cetaceans (Order Cetacea), usually in response to the environment. Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the size, shape or physiological activity including disease and parasite infection status of cetaceans (Order Cetacea). Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing rocks on the basis of physical characteristics such as colour, structure, mineralogy and grain size

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to human built structures on the coast or offshore and their impact on the environment.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the elucidation of geological structure by quantifying the proportion of waves from a high energy source reflected by sub-surface layers.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the elucidation of geological structure by quantifying the refration of waves from a high energy source by sub-surface layers.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the elucidation of sediment structure by quantifying the proportion of waves from a low energy source reflected by sub-surface layers.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the intensity of ultra-violet radiation in either the atmosphere or the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the extent of light penetration into the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the rate of electromagnetic radiation intensity decrease as it travels through the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the measurement of the Earth's gravity field

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters specifying the speed and direction of sea or land ice and the stresses associated with this motion.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the nature and intensity of light generated by biological activity in the water column.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Chemical analyses of minerals extracted from rocks or sediment or analysed in-situ using techniques like the electron microprobe.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Raw concentration parameters from a gas analyser such as a LiCor

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measurements and predictions of the displacement of the water column surface from a fixed, stable reference

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Faecal pellet production and gut evacuation rates

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the flow of electrical current through or the electrical resistance of a body of water at any point between the bed and the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the concentration of sodium chloride in any body of water at any point between the bed and the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Temperature parameters in any body of water at any point between the bed and the atmosphere excluding the top few microns sampled by radiometers known as the skin

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the ingestion of food by zooplankton (mesozooplankton and larger but excluding fish) in terms of identified biota or chemical species and the effects of nutrition on life processes such as physiology and reproduction.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All parameters associated with coastal landforms such as beaches and dunes including morphology, evolution and associated transport phenomena

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All parameters associated with radioactivity in either whole organisms or their constituent parts

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measurements of air pressure as the dependent variable (ie excluding air pressure measured to specify the z co-ordinate of a balloon or sonde), including derived parameters such as tendency (rate of change) and related parameters such as air density.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to forces due to interactions between atmosphere and the surface of the earth or between atmospheric air masses

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying heat exchange between any body of water and the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Nitrate concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in the water column. Includes nitrate+nitrite, which is often loosely referred to as nitrate.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters expressing the velocity (including scalar speeds and directions) of water column horizontal movement, commonly termed Eulerian currents

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters expressing the mean nett transport rates within the water column like Lagrangian currents. Note this is an unintentional duplicate of VDFC.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Macroalgae (Rhodophycota, Chromphycota, Chlorophycota) and seagrass (Charophyta, Anthophyta) count parameters presented at the level of taxa at any level from sub-species upwards. Count includes presence/absence indicators.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Morphological parameters of zooplankton and zoobenthos (essentially any animal except for insects, earthworms or fish), such as size, shape and weight.  Benthic and planktonic animals have not been seggregated because there is a degree of overlap (eg shrimps).

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Depth of the water column or elevation of land surface relative to sea surface, geoid or other datum

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fluxes of chemical species from the atmosphere to sea or land surface including precipitation and aerosol deposition but excluding fluxes due to exchange of gases

labels.name: definition
labels.original: A technique for mapping the morphology of the seafloor using a sonar swath projected sideways from a towed underwater vehicle.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measured or stratigraphically estimated ages of secondary mineral deposits in caves. This includes stalactites, stalagmites, flowstone, and crystal growths.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measurements of wave height that are not based on the statistical analysis of wave records, such as heave, surface roughness and visual height estimates

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to all kinds of precipitation (rain, snow, etc.) and water loss from the surface of the Earth

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of total, organic and inorganic carbon per unit weight of sediment.  Sediment is understood to be the solid phase of the bed, including the recently settled material sometimes known as fluff collected from the bed surface.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Quantity of any inorganic species such as silicon (opal) and phosphorus passing through unit area of the water column in unit time. Carbon and nitrogen are regarded as organic and explicitly excluded

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters associated with the concentration of algae-generated toxins in either whole organisms or their constituent parts

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters associated with the measurement of ocean colour, including visible waveband satellite spectral radiometer measurements, their calibration measurements (spectral water-leaving radiance and reflectance) and chart colour estimates.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes visible waveband measurements at discrete wavelengths and PAR integrated values as photon and energy fluxes. Does not include satellite radiometer and associated calibration parameters (e.g. water-leaving radiance and reflectance)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Ozone and oxygen concentration parameters in any phase of the atmosphere (but usually the gaseous phase)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: CO and CO2 concentration parameters in any phase of the atmosphere (but usuall the gaseous phase). Includes pCO2.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration of sulphur species (element or compounds) in any phase of the atmosphere. Includes sulphur dioxide.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of total, organic and inorganic carbon per unit weight of suspended particulate material collected by water column filtration, centrifugation or sediment trapping.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the mapping of terrestrial features, including coastlines

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the water held by land masses such as soil and vegetation moisture content

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying and categorising the particulate phases (solids and aerosols) of the atmosphere, excluding chemical composition

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to land (including marshes and the intertidal zone) vegetation

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to land surface temperature including fire and other hot spot location

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to atmospheric clarity, such as optical transmittance/attenuance, and resultant visibility

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measured or stratigraphically estimated age of ice

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any fauna (class Animalia) abundance per unit are of sea, river or lake bed.  Broad group overlapping a number of more specific groups that should be used preferentially, but this group is provided as an alternative to one-to-many mappings.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration of inorganic phosphorus species (element or compounds) in any phase of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration of inorganic silicon species (element or compounds) in any phase of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Technical parameters that provide information on how well an instrument or data acquisition system is working

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) protein biomass per unit volume for entities that have been identified by taxonomic name

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) protein biomass per unit volume for entities that have not been identified by taxonomic name

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters pertaining to zooplankton growth rates including biochemical proxies such as AARS activity

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Chemical composition of zooplankton expressed in terms of mass (or molar quantity) per specimen or per unit tissue mass

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Direct output parameters from spectophotometric or chemical in-situ nutrient analysers

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to bacterial production determination by measurement of dissolved organic molecule (e.g. leucine, thymidine) uptake rates

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters measured by variable fluorescence instruments such as pump and probe and fast repetition rate fluorometers

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all SPM grain size measurements and derived statistics

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that do not easily fit into any of the other SPM data categories.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of total and organic phosphorus in the particulate phase of the water column, which is a function of both the SPM concentration in the water column and the concentration of phosphorus per unit weight of SPM.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fluxes of terrestrial biological or lithological material

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration of total (organic plus inorganic) or organic dissolved phosphorus per unit volume of the water column. Grouped together as organic phosphorus frequently determined as total phosphorus.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration of total (organic plus inorganic) or organic dissolved nitrogen per unit volume of the water column.  Grouped together as organic nitrogen frequently determined as total nitrogen.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All dissolved oxygen parameters (including saturation and utilisation) for the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all pigments that cannot be explicitly classified as chlorophylls, phaeopigments or carotenoids (usually groups of pigments). Sediment includes anything collected by a grab or corer, including the fluff layer from the top of the consolidated sediment.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration of phycobolin group pigments such as phycocyanin and phycoerythrin in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Vertical water movement parameters including non-directional speeds

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the horizontal and vertical extent of cloud cover

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All parameters relating to horizontal platform travel, including distance run

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Data record, event, sample or measurement reference numbers

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Reduction rates of any species in sediment cores

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any parameter relating to the rate of DOC concentration change in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the rates of TCO2 production and consumption based on light/dark bottle incubations

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters expressing the total sedimentation flux in terms of particle mass, volume or counts

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the exchange of metalsbetween the bed (ie the sediment) and the water column sometimes termed benthic fluxes

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the exchange of nutrients between the bed (ie the sediment) and the water column sometimes termed benthic fluxes

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Flux of biological detritus (material derived from the water column such as exuvia and faecal pellets) in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that either quantify the water content of moist air or are specifically used in its determination (eg wet bulb air temperature)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of both organic (eg amines) and inorganic (eg ammonia and oxides of nitrogen) nitrogen species in all phases of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying and categorising terrestrially-derived detritus (eg dust and pollen) in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying and categorising biological detritus (eg exuvia and faecal pellets) in the water column that have been derived from the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the abundance, size and morphology of particle aggregates in the SPM

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying SPM concentration in the water column by weight, by volume or in terms of turbidity

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the size, shape and form of microfossils in sediment samples

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters quantifying the critera for and extent of sediment resuspension

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Sediment porosity (water content by volume) and water content by weight parameters

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters as logged by measuring devices, including raw counts/voltages and ADCP relative velocities

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Data parameters that carry information relating to a measured parameter such as measurement temperatures, integration depths, quantities sampled and incubation durations

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters expressing depth (possibly as pressure) of an instrument on a suspended underwater mooring.  These are primarily collected to monitor mooring performance by quantifying knock-down and should not be regarded as instrument z co-ordinates (accurate calibration is rare) or as sea level measurements.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Direct measurements (including visual estimates) plus statistically derived parameters

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the transport of material, heat or energy in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing or predicting water column structure plus parameters quantifying the dynamic stability of that structure

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measured parameters expressing turbulence in the water column plus parameters derived from these measurements

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Absolute determinations of water column density plus parameters (generally expressed as density anomaly) derived from temperature and salinity

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that describe the displacement of platforms or instruments in space relative to various origins

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for silicon species (including opal) in SPM (material gathered by filtration or sediment trapping). Only includes parameters expressed per unit mass of SPM and not per unit volume of the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for silicon species (including opal) in all phases of the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for inorganic sulphur species in suspended particulate material (anything collected by filtration or sediment trapping).  Group does not include parameters expressing data per unit volume of the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters for inorganic sulphur species in sediment (anything collected by a corer including fluff)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters (including saturation if gaseous) for inorganic sulphur species in all phases of the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentration parameters (including saturation if gaseous) for inorganic sulphur species in all phases of sediment pore waters

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of proteins in all phases of the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of proteins per unit mass or unit volume of sediment (material collected by a corer including fluff)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of adenylates (ADP, ATP etc) per unit mass or unit volume of sediment (material collected by a corer including fluff)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Alkanamine concentrations in all phases of the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters concerned with the complexation of metals as ligands in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Distribution coefficients of species between the dissolved and particulate phases of the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Raw parameters (usually membrane current and temperature) from dissolved oxygen sensors

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All concentration parameters including saturations and statistics such as standard deviations

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of total, organic and inorganic phosphorus per unit weight of suspended particulate material collected by water column filtration, centrifugation or sediment trapping.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of total and organic nitrogen in the particulate phase of the water column, which is a function of both the SPM concentration in the water column and the concentration of nitrogen per unit weight of SPM. Note that it is commonly assumed that all particulate nitrogen is organic.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of total, organic and inorganic nitrogen per unit weight of sediment.  Sediment is understood to be the solid phase of the bed, including the recently settled material sometimes known as fluff collected from the bed surface.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of total, organic and inorganic nitrogen per unit weight of suspended particulate material collected by water column filtration, centrifugation or sediment trapping.  Note that it is common practice to assume all nitrogen in SPM is organic.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Colloidal organic carbon per unit volume of the water column.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Statistical parameters derived from wave records to express wave height and period.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters for directional and non-directional spectral wave data, excluding wave directions derived from spectral data.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Alkene and alkyne concentrations in all phases of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Alkene and alkyne concentrations in all phases of the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes measurements at discrete wavelengths and PAR integrated values, measurements as photon and energy fluxes.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Temperature of the water column surface as measured by a radiometer.  It does NOT include temperature measurements in the upper few metres of the water column such as thermosalinograph data

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters related to the rates of oxygen production and consumption

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the rates of creation and consumption of organic sulphur compounds (such as DMS and carbonyl sulphide) in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters relating to the uptake rates of metals from the dissolved phase into the particulate phase

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all parameters relating to all mechanisms of waste release except respiration.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all pigments that cannot be explicitly classified as chlorophylls, phaeopigments or carotenoids.  Generally, these are parameters where different pigments have been grouped together. Concentrations are expressed in terms of per unit volume or unit area of the water column.  Does not include data expressed per unit mass of SPM.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all variants of phaeopigment (chlorophyll degradation products). Sediment is defined as any solids collected by a corer, including fluff..

labels.name: definition
