labels.original: Includes all variants of phaeopigment (chlorophyll degradation products) expressed in terms of per unit volume or unit area of the water column.  Does not include data expressed per unit mass of SPM.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Sediment includes anything collected by a grab or corer, including the fluff layer from the top of the consolidated sediment

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all variants of chlorophyll.  Sediment includes anything collected by a grab or corer, including the fluff layer from the top of the consolidated sediment

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Includes all parameters covering the strength of acoustic signal return, including absolute measurements of returning signal strength as well as parameters expressed as backscatter (the proportion of transmitted signal returned)

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Alkane concentrations in all phases of the atmosphere

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Alkane concentration parameters (including saturation of gaseous species) in all phases of the water column.  Does not include parameters expressed per unit weight of SPM.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: PAH concentrations in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff'

labels.name: definition
labels.original: 'Other' organic contaminant (substances regarded as harmful other than PCBs and PAHs) concentrations in suspended particulate material, regarded as anything sampled by a water bottle, SAP, sediment trap etc.  This group is for SPM composition measurements (concentration per unit weight) and NOT concentrations per unit volume of the water column in the particulate phase.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: PCB concentrations in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff'

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Silicate concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Urea concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Phosphate  concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Nitrite concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of dissolved organic carbon in sediment pore waters

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Nutrient (nitrate, nitrite, ammonium, phosphate, silicate and urea) concentrations in sediment pore waters

labels.name: definition
labels.original: DOC per unit volume of the water column.  Note that this includes some parameters that are strictly defined as total carbon, because the water was unfiltered on the assumption that POC was negligible.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fluxes expressed as number per unit area per unit time of any biota or remains thereof (excluding faecal pellets which are classed as SPM) downwards through the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Fluxes of any biota or remains thereof (excluding faecal pellets which are classed as SPM) downwards through the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of metal elements in the colloidal phase of the water column. Usually the dissolved concentration difference between conventionally filtered water and ultra-filtered water.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of metal elements in the dissolved phase of the water column.  This may include a contribution from the particulate phase if this has not been totally removed by filtration and the metal in question is reactive (ie detected as if it were dissolved) to the analytical technique used.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of metal elements in sediment pore waters

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any parameters relating to molecular biology or genetics

labels.name: definition
labels.original: PAH concentrations in either whole organisms or their constituent parts

labels.name: definition
labels.original: 'Other'  (than metals or organic contaminants) substance concentrations in either whole organisms or their constituent parts.  This is a 'bucket' grouping that may be reclassified as the dictionary developes.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: PCB concentrations in either whole organisms or their constituent parts

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Any zoobenthos wet weight biomass per unit area of the seabed parameters that are not included in parameter group ZWTX.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton and larger, exclusing fish, mammals, reptiles and insects) biomass determined by drying to constant weight.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton and larger, exclusing fish, mammals, reptiles and insects) biomass determined by gravimetric measurement of loss on ignition

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) carbon biomass per unit volume parameters not included in group ZCTC.  Usually used for generic names such as 'mesozooplankton'.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) abundance per unit volume parameters not included in group ZATX.  Usually used for generic names such as 'mesozooplankton'.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters that express the consumption of the phytoplankton population by the microzooplankton.  Generally the results of dilution experiments on water samples screened through a 200-micron mesh.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Basically, any microzooplankton carbon biomass measurement that isn't included in parameter group MATC.  May include data integrations such as 'total microzooplankton'.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters describing the size, shape or physiological activity of bacteria, defined as Kingdom Monera (includes cyanobacteria).  Includes parameters both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All vertical spatial parameters including depth, height and pressure when used as an independent variable.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All forms of horizontal spatial coordinates such as lat/lon and grid references

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Output as logged from any type fluorometer.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Direct output parameters from TS instruments such as thermosalinograph or CTD

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Used for plankton carbon biomass parameters where no differentiation between phytoplankton, microzooplankton or zooplankton is possible

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Total concentration of all dissolved inorganic nitrogen species in the water column, usually derived by summation of individual nutrient concentrations (NO3+NO2+NH4). Some workers may also include urea.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measurements of optical visibility in the water column

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Measured or stratigraphically estimated ages of marine sediments

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Integrated zooplankton (mesozooplankton and larger, exclusing fish, mammals, reptiles and insects) carbon biomass parameters

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of total and organic carbon in the particulate phase of the water column as extracted by a filtration technique. This is the particle-bound concentration per unit volume of the water column and is both a function of the SPM concentration in the water column and the concentration of carbon per unit weight of SPM.  Total and organic carbon are classed together to circumvent confusion caused by total carbon data sets labelled 'POC' on the assumption that the inorganic carbon fraction is negligible

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Concentrations of inorganic carbon in the particulate phase of the water column as extracted by a fitration technique.  This is the particle-bound concentration per unit volume of the water column. Consequently, it is both a function of the SPM concentration in the water column and the concentration of inorganic carbon per unit weight of the SPM.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Used for plankton abundance parameters where no differentiation between phytoplankton, microzooplankton or zooplankton is possible

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters associated with the quantification of primary production.  This is defined as the fixation of carbon dioxide into either organic or inorganic carbon by living entities and so includes photosynthesis and calcification.

labels.name: definition
labels.original: Parameters expressing the variation of temperature in the water column either as a function of space or of time

labels.name: definition
labels.original: All parameters related to zooplankton reproduction rates
